HEADWORD: Syndactylous
<hw>Syn*dac"tyl*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the toes firmly united together for some distance, and
without an intermediate web, as the kingfishers; gressorial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

